<title>USA: Oklahoma to make tobacco announcement.</title>
<headline>Oklahoma to make tobacco announcement.</headline>
<dateline>OKLAHOMA CITY, Okla. 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Oklahoma Attorney General Gerald Adams has set a news conference for 12:30 EDT Thursday regarding tobacco litigation.</p>
<p>Sources involved with other attorneys general who have sued the tobacco industry to recoup health care costs of treating smokers say Adams plans to announce that he has filed a similar case.</p>
<p>If Oklahoma sues the industry, it will become the 14th state to take such an action. Three other states, Kansas, Arizona and Michigan, also filed lawsuits this week.</p>
